# Typography & Text Sizing (Bonsai Branding)

All text in the UI must use the following roles and sizes. Use the semantic utility classes so typography stays consistent and responsive.

## Breakpoints

- **Tablet/Mobile**: Default (no prefix) – viewport &lt; 1024px
- **Desktop**: `lg:` (Tailwind) – viewport ≥ 1024px

## Text Roles and Sizes

| Role | Tablet/Mobile | Desktop | Usage |
|------|----------------|---------|--------|
| **Page title** | 28px | 36px | Main `<h1>` on each page/section |
| **Default body** | 16px | 18px | Paragraphs, form input values, button labels, main content |
| **Secondary** | 14px | 16px | Labels, captions, metadata, helper text, placeholders |

## Implementation

### Semantic classes (preferred)

Use the global utility classes defined in `src/index.css`:

- **Page titles**: `text-page-title` (plus `font-bold` and `text-bonsai-brown-700` as needed)
- **Default body text**: `text-body`
- **Secondary text**: `text-secondary` (labels, captions, hints, metadata)

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Page title
<h1 className="text-page-title font-bold text-bonsai-brown-700 mb-6">Section Name</h1>

// ✅ GOOD: Body content
<p className="text-body text-bonsai-slate-700">{description}</p>

// ✅ GOOD: Labels and secondary info
<label className="text-secondary font-medium text-bonsai-slate-700">Field name</label>
<span className="text-secondary text-bonsai-slate-500">Optional hint</span>
```

### Tailwind equivalents (when semantic class is not used)

If you need inline sizes instead of the semantic class:

- **Page title**: `text-[28px] lg:text-[36px]`
- **Body**: `text-base lg:text-lg` (16px → 18px)
- **Secondary**: `text-sm lg:text-base` (14px → 16px)

## Rules for New and Updated UI

1. **Page/section `<h1>`**: Always use `text-page-title` (and keep `font-bold text-bonsai-brown-700` for consistency).
2. **Paragraphs and main content**: Use `text-body`.
3. **Form labels, captions, hints, metadata**: Use `text-secondary`.
4. **Modal/dialog titles**: Use `text-body font-semibold` (not page-title; modals are not full pages).
5. **Buttons and inputs**: Shared components already use `text-body` (responsive) and `text-secondary` for labels; when adding new controls, follow the same pattern.
6. **Do not** use arbitrary fixed sizes (e.g. `text-xl`, `text-2xl`) for page titles or body/secondary text; use the semantic classes or the Tailwind equivalents above so that tablet/mobile vs desktop sizing stays consistent.

